Called as preview frames are displayed. This callback is invoked on the event thread open(int) was called from.

Installs a callback to be invoked for every preview frame in addition to displaying them on the screen. The callback will be repeatedly called for as long as preview is active. This method can be called at any time, even while preview is live. Any other preview callbacks are overridden. If you are using the preview data to create video or still images, strongly consider using android.media.MediaActionSound to properly indicate image capture or recording startstop to the user. Params: cb – a callback object that receives a copy of each preview frame, or null to stop receiving callbacks. Throws: RuntimeException – if release() has been called on this Camera instance.
